Quoy qu'il en ſoit, what ſoeuer it bee.
Auoir bien dequoy, Too haue ſomewhat to take too, to be rich.
RAbaiſſer vne perſonne qui s'eſleuoit trop, to pluck one downe that was to preſumptuous.
Rabbatre du pris, too abate the priſe.
Rabbatre de la ſomme & dimi nuer, to abate of the ſumme.
Rabailler & racouſtrer vn habillement, to mend a garmēt.
Rabiliter, ou Reabiliter, to repayre, to amend.
Vn Rable, ou rabot à meſler l'arene & le ſable parmi la chaulx, A ſiue ſuch as plaſtrers vſe to ſift their lime in.
Le Rable d'vn lieure, the loyne of a hare.
Le Rable d'vn sāglier, the loyne of a wild bore.
Raboter, to plane, to make ſmooth.
La Racaille du peuple, the raſcall ſort of the people.
Se Racorder & raillier, to agree againe togither.
Se Racourcir, to ſhrinke togither or to ſtoope.
Raccouſtrer, to mende, to trim agayne.
Raccouſtumer, ou Ramener quelque couſtume, to bring a custome agayn, to bring in vre agayne.
Vn Race, a race, an ofspring, a kindred.
Racheter au poix de l'or, to redeme with the weight of gold.
Rachet, ou payemēt de rançon a redeeming or paying of ranſome.
Racler, to rake, to ſcrape, too grate.
Vn Racloir, a grater, a ſcraper.
Raconteurs de nouuelles, tellers of newes.
Radoter, to deceyue or ſet one in dotage.

Radreſſer ou Redreſſer, too amend,
to correct.
Se Raduiſer, to take better aduiſement, to change aduiſe.
La Raffle d'vne grappe de Raſin, the ſtalke of a bunche of grapes.
Rafreſchir, to refreſh, to cheare vp.
Rager & folatrer, too playe the wanton, to ticke and toye.
Raggrandir, to enlarge, to make great.
Railler & ſe gaudir d'aucun, to iest or to floute.
Vn Railleur ou Raillard, A Jester.
Rainſeaux ou Rameaux d'arbres, bowes of trees.
Vne grappe de Raiſin, a bunche of grapes.
A quelle Raiſon? by what reaſon?
C'eſt la Raiſon, it is reaſon.
Ce qui eſt Raiſonnable, that which is reaſonable.
ce n'eſt pas faict Raiſonnablement a toy, it is not reaſonably done of thee.
Ramage, Les petits oiſeaux oublient leur Ramage, The branche ſong of byrds.
Ramas & meſlange, A gathering togither, a medley.
Rame de papier, a reme of paper
Rameau, a branche of a tree, a bowe.
Ramenteuoir, to remēber, to put in remembrance.
Vne Rame ou auiron, an oare.
Ramer, tirer à l'auiron, Too rowe.
Ramier, ou coulomb Ramier, a ſtocke doue.
Ramon, ou Ballay, a brome, a beſome.
Ramper ou grimper, to rampe, or climbe.
Rampement & trainement ſur le ventre ou pieds ſur terre, a ramping or creeping on the ground.
Ramu, ou branché, full of bowes.
Ranci, relant, chanſi, morſi, rustie, musty, fuſty.
s'enfuir à grand Randon, to run away in hast.
Ranger, ou Arranger, to ſette in order, to range.
Vne Rangée de Rames ou auirons, a rowe of oares.
Vn Rape, A Raspe or roughe Fyle.
Rapetacer, & reamender, To patch, to peece.
Rappel, a calling agayne, an appeale.
Faire Rapporter vne choſe à vn autre, too make one thing agree with an other.
Ce champ Rapporte & rend beaucoup, this fielde yeldeth much frute.
Se Rapporter à aucun, to report himſelfe to any man.
Rapporter tout à aucun, Mettre tout entre les mains d'aucuns, to report all to one man, to put al into his hands.
Grand Rapport de terre, great yeelding ground.
Rapporteurs de parolles, reporters of wordes.
Faulx Rapporteur, a falſe reporter, a backebyter.
Rapt, ou Rauiſſemēt, rauiſhing or taking away by violence.
Rare, qui ne ſe trouue, ou ne ſe void point ſouuent, ne par tout, rare, geaſon, dainty.
Raſure & effaceure de lettres ou mots, raſing out of words.
Raſſaſier, to ſatisfie, to content ones appetit.
Raſsēbler, rabiller, raccouſtrer quelque choſe bien proprement, to ſet togither, to mende a thing finely.
Qui eſt poſé & Raſſis, a ſettled man.
Raſteler le bled en herbe, To rake the corne while it is grene
Ratifier, & approuuer, to ratifie, to approue.
Raton, ou petit rat, a yong rat.
Ratteindre en cheminant, To ouertake in going.
Faire vn Rauage, to make a rode on the enimies.
Raualler, rehumer, to ſwallowe downe againe.
Rauellement & amoindriſſement, a falling in price, as the falling of the market.
Rauaudeur qui refait les vieux habillements, a botcher.
Vne Raue, a rape, or turnop.
Rauine ou Ragaz d'eaue, great flouds of water.
Rauir, to rauiſhe, to take away by violence, to rob.
Se Rauoir, to come agayn to him ſelfe.
Vn Ray ou rayon de ſoleil, the beame of the Sunne.
Vn Rayon pour eſcouler l'eaue d'vne champ, a drane to drawe the water out of a fielde.
Vne Raye, ou ligne, a rowe, or ligne.
Rayer, Effacer, to raſe, to croſſe oute.
Reaument & de faict, verily, in deede.
Rebailler forme à quelq̄ choſe to newe make a thing.
Il a Rebecqué contre moy, He ſtoode with me face to face.
Reboucher ou Emouſſer vn trenchant ou pointe, to bluntē the edge or point of a thing.
Reboucher vn trou, to ſtop vp a hole.
A Rebours, arſward, quite contrary, backeward.
Couler à rebours, To flowe ageinſt
Reduire à neant, To bryng to naught.
Reduire en pouldre, To bryng to dust.
Refaire les portes qui ſont rō pues, to mende broken gates, to make newe.
Vn Refort ou raue, a rape, a radiſhe.
Refouler le trenchant de quelque choſe, to blunten the edge of a thing.
Refoulement, an abating of the edge.
Refrains des balades, the burthen of a ſong.
Se refraindre & moderer, To refrayne, to forbeare.
Refrener la hardieſſe d'aucun, to abate the boldneſſe of one.
Refrigerer. &c. Vſés de refroidir, proprement ſe dit d'vne choſe qui par auant boulloit, to coole.
Refuiant le labeur, fleeing from labour.
Refuſer, to refuſe, to denye, to gaynſay, to forſake.
Eſtre refuſe, to be refuſed or forſaken.
Refus qu'on fait d'aucun, The refuſing of any perſon.
Regain, foin derriere ſaiſon, aftercrop of hay.
Regarder, to regarde, to marke, to ſee, to looke, to espy.
Se regarder & glorifier, to ſette muche by himſelfe.
Regent, a regent, a ſcholemaiſter, a gouernour.
Regimber, To winſe, to kicke and fling.
Vn Regime de viure, an order of diet.
Region, a Region, a realme, a countrey.
Regir & gouerner, to rule and gouerne.
Regorger, to giue vp againe, to parbreake.
Regorgement & trop grande abondance, exceſſe, too great abundance.
Regratter quelque vielle robbe, & la faire comme neuue to newe dreſſe an olde gowne
Regrateurs, ou regratier, dreſſers of olde clothes.
Regratement de vieilles choſes pour les mieux vendre apres, the flouriſhing vp of old things to make them better to ſale.
Regrediller les cheueux, To friſell the heare.
Regretter aucun, To bewayle one, to be ſory for one.
Rehoüement, a newe digging as they doo yearely aboute the rootes of vines.
Reiecter, to reiect, to despiſe, to cast of.
Reiecter tout vn affaire au mois de Mars, To put off all a buſineſſe till March.
Vn reiecton, the yong ſpring of a vine.
Reigler les choſes, To rule things.
Reiglement & ancienne obſeruance, a rule and auncient custome.
Le Rein, ou roignon, The kidneye.
La raine d'vne bride, the reyns of a bridle.
Relaſchement de labeur, leauing of worke
Relater, pour reciter, to ſhewe forth, to recite.
Releguer, Bannir, ou confiner, to banniſhe.
Le Relief ou demourat du ſouper ou diſner, the remnant of a ſupper, or that which is left.
Relier des liures, to bynd bokes.
Relier vn muy ou cuuier, to hoope a tubbe.
La Reliqua qu'on doibt d'aucun, the rest of any ſumme.
Reluire, to ſhine, to haue a gloſſe, to glister.
Remanent, the remnant which is lefte.
Remanier, to take in hande againe.
Remaſchement, a chawing of the cudde.
Remboiſter vn os, to ſet a bone that is out of ioynt.
Rembourſer les deniers deſpē duz en la guerre, to purſe the money againe that we ſpent in the warre.
Relais, ſeates or banks to ſit on.
R'embrouſſer chemin, to take the next way.
Remener, ou Ramener, to bring againe.
Remettre, to place aright, to reſtore to the first eſtate.
Remettre la peine, to forgiue the payne.
Remettre à aucun ſa faulte, & l'en reprendre aigrement, to reproue one for his faulte, to checke.
Rencheoir en maladie, To fall ſicke againe.
Rançonner & piller aucun, to ranſome or poll one.
Rencontreur, qui ſe mocque d'autruy, mocqueur, a ſcoffer.
Se Rendormir, to fall a ſleepe agayne.
Rendormiſſement, a falling againe on ſleepe.
Se Rendre à aucun en ſa ſauegarde & puiſſance, to yeld to the ſauegard and power of an other.
Renforcir, to waxe ſtronge, to take a good courage.
Enuoyer du renfort, to ſend aid
Se renfrongner, To frowne, to skoule.
Rengreger vn mal, to make a thing worſe than it is.
Renier auec ſerment, to denye with othe.
Reniement de la choſe deüe, to deny a due.
Renoncer aucun à gendre, to forſake one for his kinne.
Renoncer à l'amitié d'aucun, to forſake frendſhip with one.
Renouer les choſes delaiſſées & rompues, to knit vp things that are a ſunder.
Renouuele, racouſtré, & regratté, renued, new trimmed.
Rentraire, to lay in a ſeam with a nayle.
Coup donné à la Renuerſe, a croſſeblow.
Repaire & logis, a place to repaire to, a loding.
Repaiſtre & bailler à manger, to feede.
Prendre ſon repas, To take repaste.
Repaſſer la mer, par ou on eſtoit venu, to paſſe agayne ouer ſea.
Penſer & repenſer en ſon eſprit, to think and think again.
Repenſement, a chewing of the cudde.
Soy repentir d'auoir fait quelque choſe, to repent of doing a thing.
Repeter & redire vn meſme choſe, to repete or ſay oft one thyng.
Repetition de quelque choſe, the repetition of any thing.
Replanter, to plant or ſet vp againe.
Replier, to bend againe, to folde againe.
Repos d'eſprit, quiete mynde, peace of conſcience.
Repoſer & dormir, to rest and ſleape.
Se Repoſer, to reſt, to take eaſe.
Reprendre, to receyue againe, to take againe.
Faire reprēdre les choſes rompues, To make broken thyngs holde togither ageyne.
Reprendre aucun de quelque faulte, to reproue one of ſome fault committed.
Repreſenter, To repreſente, to kepe the place.
Ie vous prie, & reprie, J pray and pray you againe.
Repudier ſa femme, to forſake his wyfe.
Repugner, contredire, aller alē contre, to repugne, to gaynſay.
Reputer aucun pour tel, ou tel, to repute or esteeme one for ſuch.
Bonne Reputation, good reputation and estimation.
Mauuaiſe Reputation, ill reputation or name.
Requerir, to require instantly, to deſire.
Racine fort Requiſe pour faire onguent, an excellent roote to make oyntement.
Faire Requeſte à aucū, to make requeste to one.
Reſchaper d'vne maladie, to eſcape or recouer a ſickneſſe.
Reſchauffoir ou Reſchault, A chaſing diſh.
Reſcinder vn cōtract, to breake a bargayne.
Se Recourre du danger ou on eſtoit d'eſtre mis en oubly, to ſeeke to forget danger.
Le Reſcript & lettres d'vn Prince, the aunſwere of a Prince by letter.
Reſembler, to reſemble, to bee like.
Ne Reſemblant rien à vn autre, nothing reſembling an other.
Reſemblance faicte ſur le vif, a counterfeate made after the lyfe.
Reſequer & oſter du tout, to cut it wholly off.
Reſerrer, to ſhut vp, to cloſe.
Reſeruoir, a cloſet too keepe things in.
Reſider, eſtre long temps aſſis, to bee reſident, or to ſitte long.
Reſigner, renoncer & quicter ſon office, to reſigne, too renounce, to giue ouer.

Reſine, vne humeur coulante, principalement du pin, & ••
autres herbes, roſin.

Reſiouir, to reioyce, to make one
merry, to bee merry.
Se Reſiouir, to be gladde, to bee ioyfull, to be merry.
Tu m'as tout Reſiouy, thou haſt lightned my hart.
Reſiſter, to reſist, to withstand, to repugne.
Ie ſuis Reſolu à cela, J am reſolued thereto.
C'eſt ma Reſolution, Voylace qu'il m'enſemble, this is my reſolution or aduiſe.
Reſortir en la cour, to demand right in Court.
Reſouldre, to reſolue, to breake or vndoe.
Faire Reſouldre les humeurs du corps, to reſolue the humours in mans body.
Reſpandre ça & là, Too ſpread abroade.
Reſpandre le vin, Too ſhed wyne.
Les parties ont Reſpectiuement appellé, the parties haue on both ſides appealed.
Reſpirer, to gaspe or fetch ones breth.
Reſplendir, to ſhine, to glister, to glimſe.
Reſpondre de quelque argent, ou aultre choſe, to bee ſuertie for money or other things.
Vn Reſpondant ou pleige, A ſuertie.
Reſponſes, herbe, a little roote that is eaten in ſallades.
Reſtaurer, to restore, to repaire, to renewe.
Reſter, to remayne, or to reast behind.
Reſtituer, to restore, to yeeld agayne.
Reſtrainct & ſerré, ou arreſté, restrained and cloſed vp.
Reſueiller, to waken or to ſtirre vp.
Reſuſciter, to rayſe from death to lyfe.
Retarder, ou Retarger, Too driue off, to ſlacken, to defer, to hinder.
Retentir, to ſounde agayne, too giue an eccho.
Beſte Retiue & qui rue, a resty horſe.
Retirer en arriere, Too drawe backward.
Retirer ce qu'on donne, too receyue in that which is giuen.
Retirer à quelqu'vn, & luy reſembler, to be lyke one in condition.
Retirer à ſoy & derobber, Too ſcratch to himſelf, to ſteale.
Se Retirer à part, to withdrawe aſyde.
Retirement, ou Retraction, A recanting or calling backe of wordes ſpoken, a retractation.
Retiſtre ce qui eſt detiſſu, Too weaue agayn that which was vnwouen.
Retondir de toutes parts, Too ſound or ring on all ſydes.
Retordre, to wring, to wreth, to wrest, to twyne.
Vn Retoube, vne terre qu'on ſeme tous les ans, a fielde that is ſowen euery yeare.
Retourner, to retourne, to come backe agayne.
Retracter & reuoir, to correcte a thing and ouerſee a thing.
Vn priué & Retraict, a priuie or houſe of office.
Vn Retraict public, a common priuie.
Sonner à la Retraicte, to ſound the retyre.
Retraire en ſeruage, to bring to bondage.
Retrecir, Too pull or drawe backe.
Retrencher les gages, to cut off wages.
Reualloir, to recompenſe, too bee as much worth to him as that comes too.
Bailler la Reuanche, to bee euen with one.
Reueler, to reueale, to diſcloſe, to bewraye.
Reuēdre vne choſe auec celuy qui l'auoit vendue, too ſell a thing agayne to him that ſold it.
Vn Reuendeur & regrateur, A retayler, or huckster.
Reuenir en quelque lieu, Too come agayne into any place.
Qui Reuient bien aux gents, & n'eſt point enuieux, a fellow-like man.
Le Reuenu d'aucun, any mans rent or reuenew.
Reuoir & retracter vne choſe, to correct and ouerſee a thing.
Reuerberé, ou frappé, reflex or reuerberation.
La Reuerberation du ſoleil, the reflex of the ſun.
Reuerence qu'on porte à au cun, the reuerence that is borne to one.
Auoir en Reuerence, too haue in reuerence.
Se Reuolter & rendre du party des enemis, to reuolte, to take the enimies part.
L'an Reuolu, the yeare being gone about.
Reuoquer en doubte, to call in question or doubt.
Le Rez de chauſſée, Le ſol & fondement de toutes choſes, The foundation of any thing.
Rhetorique, l'Art & ſcience de bien & ſagement dire & parler, Rhetorique.
Conterfaire le Rheteur, Too counterfeat the rhetorician.
Couper tout Ric à Rie, to cut quite in ſunder.
Le Rideau des ioueurs de farces, the players courtin.
Les Rides qui viennent au viſage, wrincles in the face.
Se Rider & refrongner, Too frowne or lowre.
Rioiter, to ryot, to playe the ſpendthrifte.
Du Riz, ryce, whereof ryce pottage is made.
Du Ris, Ryce, a kind of grayne.
Robbe, an vpper garment, a gowne, a robe.
La Robbe d'vne femme, a womans gowne.
Vne longue Robbe, A long gowne.
Robre, ou Roure, vne eſpece de cheſne treſ-dure, a hard kind of Oke.
Roc, ou Roche, ou Rocher, A rocke or ſtone.
Roder le pays, to make a rode on the Countrey.
Vn Rodeur ou coureur, a roder or wighrider.
Eſtre Roide de froid, to be ſtiffe with colde.
Vn Roitelet, ſorte d'oiſeau, A birde called a wren.
Rompierre, Perſepierre, herbe Empetron, an herbe called Empetron.
Rompre, to breake, to burste in ſunder, to paſh in peeces.
Vn Rondeau de patiſſier, A cookes peele.
Vne petite Rondelle de guerre, a ſmall target or buckler.
Ronfler, to ſnort, to ſnore, to rowte.
Rongé tout à l'entour, knabled about.
Roquet, habillemēt de fille ou femme, a womans wastcote.
Roquette, herbe, an herbe called rocket.
De la Roſette, a colour called roſſet.
Roſtir ou cuire à la braiſe, To rost.
Rouelle d'oignon, a ſhiue of an oignion.
Rougir de honte, to bluſhe for ſhame.
Rouget, poiſſon, a fiſhe called a rotchet.
Rougeole, ou verole, the ſmall pocks.
Roule, ou Roole, a skroll, a catalogue.
Le Rouleau & racloir des meſureurs, a weauers ſhittle.
Vn Rouillier, ou voicturier, A Carriar.
Roupie, an iſſicle, the noſe dropping.
Vne Rouſſette, a fiſhe called a Barbell.
Router, to belche or breake wind
La Route du lieure, the hare furme.
Vne grande Route de gens, ou de cerfs, a route or multitude of people.
Vn vieux Routier ou Roturier, qui de long temps eſt vſité à ſineſſes, an old deceyuer.
Roytelet, A byrde called a wren.
Vn Ru, ou Reu, a brooke.
Ruben de teſte, a headband or fyllet.
Vne Ruche à miel, a Bee hyue.
Rude & aſpre à manier, rude and hard to be broken.
Rues d'vne ville, the ſtreates of a towne.
Vne Ruelle ou petite Rue, A Lane.
De la Rue, an herbe called Rue, or herbe grace.
Ruer du hault en bas, to throw downe hedlong.
Ruer par terre, to throwe downe to the ground.
Ruer des pieds, to ſtrike with the heeles, to kicke.
Le Lion Rugit, ou Ruit, The Lyon rores.
Ruiner & deſtruire, To ouerthrowe to destroye.
Ruiſſeau, a cannel, a brocke or running water.
Ruminer, cōme quand les beſtes remaſchent ce qu'elles ont ja mangé: propre aux beſtes à pied ſourché, Too chewe the kud.
Rupture, quand l'inteſtin deſcend, bursting of the coddes.
Ruſtault, ou Ruſtique, a countrey man.
Vn Sabot à ſe iouër, a toppe.
Sabots & ſouliers de bois, pattens, wodden ſhoes.
Saburre & groſſe arene dequoy on charge les nauires, à fin d'eſtre plus fermes, ſhingle, or pebble ſtones.
S'accouſter à l'oreille, too whiſper in ones eare.
Sacre, oyſeau de proye, a kinde of hauke.
Sacré à Dieu, conſecrated too God.
Sacrements, qui ſont tenus ſecrets au peuple, Sacraments.
Sacrilege, Larron des choſes ſacrées, ſacriledge, theft of holy things.
Sadayer vne femme, Too flatter a woman, or ſpeake hir fayre.
Sagitaire, ou archer, an archer, a ſhooter.
Saigner & iecter ſang, too lette bloud.
Saigner aucun, to let one bloud.
Saigneux, bloudy, or full of bloud.
Saillir, to leape, to skip, to hoppe, to daunce.
Saillie auec impetuoſité, cōme de genſdarmes ſur les ennemis, an iſſuing out, as footmen doe on their enimies.
La Saillie & cabochon d'vne pierre pretieuſe taillée en boſſe, the chaſe wherein a precious ſtone is encloſed.
Sain doulx, ſeeme or freſhe greaſe.
Sainct & ſans aucune tache de de vice, holly, vnspotted.
Saiſir les meubles d'aucū pour quelque contumace, to ſeaze or attach the goods of any mā
Saiſon & temps propre à faire quelque choſe, ſeaſon, or fitte tyme to doe any thing.
Vne Salade ou heaulme, a ſallet, or helmet.
Salades d'arbres ou autre choſes, all kinde of ſalades.
Saler, to ſalte, to ſeaſon, to pouder.
La saline, a ſalte houſe, where ſalt is made.
Salir quelque choſe, to beray a thing, to ſoyle.
Saluer aucun, to ſalute one, to greete.
Donner ſalut, salüer, To giue health.
Sandal, bois qu'on apporte d'Inde, a precious wood that is brought out of Jnde.

Tauernier vne choſe, to tauern a thing.
Vn Taureau, ou Toreau, a bull.
Taxer aucun & reprendre, too reproue or checke one.
Taxer le payement aux bataillans, to ceaſſe the payement to thoſe that fought.
Vne Taye & Tache blanche en l'oeil, a perle in the eye.
Tayes de l'oeil, ſpottes in the eies.
Vne taye d'oreillier, a pyllowe beere.
Le Tect d'vne maiſon, the couering of a houſe.
Teigne, the ſcurfe of a ſcall.
Teindre d'autre couleur que la couleur naiue, to dye into any colour.
Tempeſter, to ſtorm at a thing.
Vn Temple & eſgliſe, a church, a temple.
Les Temples, ou mieux Temps de l'homme, the Temples of a man.
Paſſer le Temps, To paſſe the time, to play.
Il eſt maintenant temps, Jt is now tyme.
Il a eſté vn temps que. &c, there was a tyme when.
Long temps deuant, long tyme before.
Vn peu de Temps, a little tyme.
Vn autre temps, an other tyme.
Du Temps de nos peres, The tyme of our fathers.
En peu de Temps, in ſmalle tyme, ſhortly.
Temporiſer, s'accommoder au temps, To agree with the tyme.
Tendre ou eſtendre, to ſtretche out, to ſpreade abroade.
Le tout tend à celá, The whole tendeth thervnto.
Cela tend en mont, that giueth vpwarde.
Ou Tendez vous, whyther walke ye?
Tendon & vuile de la vigne, the tendrell of a vine.
Tendre aux oyſeaux, to lay for birdes.
Tendu & roidi, ſtretched out and ſtiffe.
Vne Tente & pauillon, a tent or pauillion.
Qui eſt tendre, which is tender
Tendron, comme celuy de l'oreille, ou du nez, the gristle of the eare or the noſe.
Le tendron de bout des arbres ou arbreaux, the tender branches of a tree.
Tenir compte au chapiſtre des receptes, to holde accompt of ſuch things as haue ben receyued.
Ne Tenir compte de ſoy, not to care for himſelfe.
Tenir ſa promeſſe, to kepe promyſe.
Tenir propos auec quelqu'vn, to holde talke with one.
Se Tenir nettement, to kepe him ſelfe cleanly.
Se Tenir debout, to ſtande vpright, to ſtand.
Ie ne me puis tenir que. &c. J can not forbeare.
Tenir à quelque choſe, ou contre quelque choſe, to hold or cleaue to a thing.
Eſtre tenu à aucun, to be beholden to one.
Tenir contre aucun, to ſtande against one.
Tiens pour certain que. &c. holde it for certain.
Tenant & taquin, a niggarde, a ſnudge.
Le Tenans & aboutiſſans, The limittes or bounds.
Tout d'vn tenant, al of one hold
Teneur, ſuite, ou continuation, the tenour or continuation.
le Tenon ſe met en vne mortaiſe, a ſtaple.
Vne Tente qu'on met en vne playe, a tent to put in a woūd.
Tenter & eſſayer à faire quelque choſe, to attempt or aſſay to doo a thing.
Tercer, Terceer, labourer pour la troiſieme fois la terre, To till the ground the third time.
Eſtre mis en termes, to be put to termes.
En meſmes Termes, in the ſame termes or wordes.
Se Ternir, to waxe pale or wan.
Qui eſt de couleur Terne, pale.
Le territoire d'vne ville, the territories belonging to a towne.
Grand Terrien, a man of greate landes.
Vn Teſme, ou theſme, La choſe qu'on a propoſée pour en parler & diſputer, a theme.
Prendre a Teſmoing, to take to witneſſe.
Teſtateur qui à laiſſée vn laiz, a testatoure that leaueth a legacie.
Teſtu, a headestrong fellowe, a wyldebrayne.
Vn Teſtiere ou ſalade, a skull, or ſallet.
Teſtifier & dire appertement, to teſtifie and ſpeake plainely.
Teſtonner, to curle or friſle ones head.
Le Teſts de la teſte, the ſcalpe or skull of the head.
Tette, Mammelle, a dugge, a teate, a breast.
Theatre, Edifice public ou le peuple s'aſsēbloit pour voir ioüer les ieux, a theatre or cō mon place of ſhewe.
Vn threſorier de guerres, a treſorer in warres.
Treſorier de l'eſpargne, The high treaſorer.
Thun poiſſon, a kinde of fiſhe called Tunny.
Du thym, an herb called Time.
Tiede, ne chauld ne froid, luke warme.
Cela eſt Tien, that is thine.
Il eſt le Tiers, he is the thirde.
La Tige de quelque herbe que ce ſoit, the ſtalke of any herb.
Le Tillac d'vne nauire, the decking of a ſhippe.
Tillet, ou Tilleul, arbre, a Birch tree.
Vn Tiltre ou eſcripteau, qu'on fait ſus quelque choſe pour cognoſtre que c'eſt, a title writtē vpō a thing to know it.
Timon d'vn chariot, the axeltre of a cart.
Vne Tinette ou cuue a ſe baigner, a bathing tub.
Tinter & ſonner clerement, comme fait vn verre, or, ou argent, to ring as ſiluer doth.
Tont d'vne tire & continuement, all in one length.
Tirer & trainer, to drawe or trayle.
Tirer par force, to draw by force
Tirer ou mettre dehors, to draw out.
Tirer a la fin & ſe mourir, to draw on, or lie in dying.
Tirer à l'auiron, to drawe at an oare.
Se Tirer pres, to draw nigh.
Tirer les vers du nez, to creepe into a man to know his minde.
De la Tiſane, a kinde of drinke called Tiſant.
Tiſanne de ris, Tiſan made of Riſe.
Vn Tiſon allumé, a fire brande.
Tiſon de feu eſteinct, a quenched brande.
Tiſtre, faire de la toile, to weue.
Qui eſt Tiſſu, which is wouen.
Tiſſerand de toile, a linnen weauer.
Vne togue on robbe longue, a long gowne.
Le Toict & couuerture d'vne maiſō, the couering of a houſe.
Eſtre caché & ſoubs le toict, to be hidden and vnder couert.
Toiſe, a meaſure of ſixe fote lōg.
Toiſer, to meaſure with ſuch a meaſure.
Tolerer, endurer, & ſouffrir, to tolerate, to ſuffer, to beare with.
Tombe, ou Tombeau, a graue or tombe.
Tōber, to fal down, ſeke Cheoir
Tōber en vn daunger, to fall into danger.
Tombement du hault en bas, a falling downe hedlong.
Le Tonnere ou Tonnoire, the thunder.
Porter la torche, to bear a torch
Torcher, nettoyer, to wipe, to make cleane.
Vn Torchon, à Torcher les ſouliers, ou vaiſſelles, a ſhoe clout.
Torture ou gehēne, a racke or pin banke.
Tormente & Tēpeſte de vents, ſtorme or torment of winde.
Tormenter, to torment, to vexe, to grieue.
Torpille, poiſſon, a fiſhe that when it is taken, benōmeth the hands of the taker for a while.
Torrent, vne abōdance d'eaue qui par grande roideur chet des montaignes, a greate floud of water.
A Tort & ſans cauſe, wrongfully, without cauſe.
A Tort ou à droict, by right or by wrong, by one meanes or other.
Tortuement & pliement de quelque choſe, a crooking or bending of any thing.
Vne Tortue, a beast called a Tortoiſe.
Vne Toſtée, a toste of bread.
Vne piere dicte Touch, ſus laquelle on eſproue l'or, a touchſtone.
La Touche dequoy on eſcript ſus les tablettes, a penne to write on tables.
Toucher deuant ſoy, & mener ſon beſtail, to driue our beaſts before him.
Cela me touche, that toucheth me.
Touch āt cela, c'eſt ſa faulte, as for that it is his fault.
Touchant le pere, aboute his father.
Touchant ce que tu m'eſcris par tes lettres. &c. concerning that which thou writest to me in thy letters.
Vne Touffe de cheueux retors les vns entre les autres, a wē lock or locke of heare.
Touiller & meſler, to mingle, to meddle.
Touruette, Tourelle, ou Tournelle, a turret.
Vn Tour & fineſſe, a feare or pranke.
Le Tour du ſoleil, the compaſſe of the ſunne.
Le Tour d'vne ville, the cōpaſſe of the towne.
Le Tour & rond des roues, the circle of the wheele.
Vn Tour ou tournoir, a turnepike.
Tourbe, preſſe, & foulle de gēs a preaſe and thrust of people.
Tourbillon de vent, a whirle winde.
Vn Touret à cauer, a wimble or perſer.
Tourner ſon eſprit a faire quelque choſe, to turne his minde to do ſome thing.
Tourner d'vn language en vn autre, to turne out of one ſpech into an other.
Il tourne & panche vers le midy, it turneth and hangeth towardes the ſouth.
Par Tournées, Chaſcun à ſon tour, Tour à tour, by turns, or euery one in his turne.
Tournoyer, to compaſſe or go about.
Vn tournoy, ou iouſtes, a tourney or iustling.
Vn Tournois, ou denier, a penie frenche.
Vn Tourte, ou Tourterelle, A turtle doue.
Tout, all. Tout aultāt, euen as much.
Tout au plus, at the moste.
Tout ce que voudras, plutoſt q̄. &c. what thou wilt rather.
Toute, bonne ſorte d'herbe autrement dicte Oruale, an herbe like to horehound.
Trac, Nier tout à Trac, to deny it flatly.
Tracaſſeur, a buſy body, a toyler to little purpoſe.
La Trace, ſoyt d'homme ou beſte, the trace of man or beast.
Tracement, a tracing, a ſeeking for.
Traduire, Trāſlater, ou tourner d'vne langue en autre, Too tranſlate out of one ſpeach into an other.
Traiſtre & deſloyal, a traytour or an vnfaithfull perſon.
Vn Traict ou ligne, a draught or lyne.
Les Traicts des lettres, The draught of letters.
Le Traict & façon de quelque choſe, the draught or figure of any thing.
Vn Traict on dard, an arrow or dart.
Vn Traict d'are, a bowe ſhot.
Vn Traict d'eaue, a draught of water.
Traicter & manier, to treate or to handle.
Traicter aucun ſoit en bien ou en mal, to vſe or entreat one eyther wel or ill.
Traicter de quelque affaire, to entreat of certayne things.
Vn Traicté & liuret, a treatiſe or ſmall booke.
Vn Traicté & accord, a treatie and agreement.
Le Train d'aucun Prince, The trayne of a Prince.
Tout d'vn train, all in one way.
Veu le Train ou la diſpoſition en quoy eſt ton pere, ſeeing the trade that thy Father is in.
Vn Trameau, vne ſorte de rets, a tramell net.

Traire vne vache, brebis, & autres beſtes qui ont du laict,
to mylke a cowe or ſheepe.
La Traicte du laict d'vne beſte, ones meales mylke.
Tranſcrire & copier, To write out, to coppy.
Transfigurer, chāger d'vne forme en autre, to chaunge from one forme to an other.
Eſtre en Tranſe, Too bee in a traunce.
Tranſgreſſer & outrepaſſer, too tranſgreſſe, to ouerpaſſe.
Tranſi, in a ſwoune or traunce.
Eſtre Tranſi de froid, to bee almost dead for cold.
Trāſiger & appointer, to agree, to fall to a point.
Vne Tranſaction, vn accord, an agreement, an attonement.
Tranſlater, ou tourner en autre language, to tranſlate.
Tranſporter, to carry ouer, too transport.
Tranſport d'vn lieu en aultre, the transporting from one place to another.
Tranſpoſer d'vn lieu en autre, to transporte from one place to another.
Tranſpoſé, ou reiecté, trāsported or reiected.
La peine & T rauail qu'ō prend à faire quelq̄ choſe, the trauell and labor that wee take to doo a thing.
Le Trauail d'vne femme pour enfanter, the trauell of a woman in childbyrth.
Le Trauail ou les marichaux mettēt les cheuaux pour ferrer, ou autrement, that wherin the ferrer ſettels vnruly horſes to ſhoe them.
Trauailler, to trauell, to labour, to toyle.
Trauailler & ennuyer aucun, to grieue or annoye one.
Iecter au trauers, & faire paſſer de nauire en autre, to ſtryke ouerthwart.
Regarder de Trauers, to loke a skewe, to leere.
Trauerſer & percer tout oultre to pierce thorow.
Trebucher, to fal down, to offēd.
Vn Trebuchet à prendre oyſeaux, a pitfall, to catch birds in.
Vn Trebuchet à peſer or ou argent, golde weights.
Vn Tref, ou poultre, the beame of a houſe.
Treffle, herbe, an herbe called thre leaued graſſe.
Trembler, to tremble, to ſhake, to quake.
Faire Tembler, to make one quake.
Trembler de froid, to quake for colde.
Trembler de peur, to quake for feare.
La Treme, ou Traime d'vn tiſſerand, a weauers wooffe.
La Tremie d'vn moulin, The myll hopper.
Le Trenchant ou taillant d'vn ferrement, the edge of a toole.
Le Trencher d'vn courdouannier, a ſhoemakers knife.
Vn Trencheoir rond, A round trencher.
Les Trenchées, maladies de vē tre, a diſeaſe in the belly, the gnawing of the guttes.
Trepiner & danſer, to trample, to daunſe.
Mon Treſcher ami, My very deere friend.
Treſpas & la mort d'aucun, the death of one.
Treſpaſſer le commandement de Dieu, to trespaſſe the commaundement of God.
Treues & ceſſation de guerre iuſques à quelque tēps dict, truce or ceaſſing from warre for a tyme.
Vn Treangle, a triangle, that is three cornered.
Vne Tribu, c'eſtoit anciennement la trētecinquieme partie du peuple de Rome. Et la douzieme partie du peuple d'Iſraël, a tribe.
Les Tribuns qui furent creez à Rome pour empeſcher que les grans magiſtrats ne foulaſlent le peuple, the Tribunes of the people of Rome.
Trier & eſlire, ou ſeparer l'vn d'auec l'autre, to chooſe.
Vne Tringle, a fastning of two peeces of wood togither which the Carpenters call a douetayle.
Triomphe, entrée ſolennelle & magnifique qu'on faiſoit à vn Capitaine, a triumphe.
Triper & fouler aux pieds, Too tread vnder foote.
Triple victoire, triple or three fold victorie.
Tripot, ieu de paulme, a tennis court.
Triſteſſe & douleur de cueur, ſorowe, or hartgriefe.
De Triſteſſe & douleur, of ſorow and grief.
Des Troſchique, eſpece de medicine, pilles.
Troeſue, arbre ayāt les fueilles plus larges que l'Oliuer, A tree ſo called.
Trompe & muſeau d'Elephant, the ſnout of an Elephant.
Trompe, ou ſabot dequoy ſe iouent les enfants, a toppe.
Le Tronc d'vn arbre, the bodye of a tree.
Tronſon, Diminutif de Tronc, a troncheon.
Trot de cheual, the trotte of a horſe.
Trotteur, vn villotier, a trotter, a trampler.
Vne Trotiere ou coureuſe, A gadder about ſtreates, a fiſegig.
Vn Trouble, bruict & eſmeute, a trouble.
Vne choſe Trouble, a thicke or vnſettled thing.
Vne Trouppe & multitude de gents, a troupe or multitude of people.
Troupeau de beſtes menues ou groſſes, a flocke of any kind of beastes, a heard.
Troupeau de beſtial, a flocke of cattell.

Par Troupeaux & bandes, By
heapes and bandes.
Vne Trouſſoire, a girdle, a belt.
Vne Trouſſe, ou Carquois, A quyuer.
Trouſſer ſa robbe, too tucke or truſſe vp his gowne.
Trouuer à la Trace, ou aupres auoir bien cerché, to finde by the trace.
Trouuer en chemin, to find by the waye.
Trouué ſur le faict, taken with the deed doing.
Truffes ou ſaligots & chaſtaignes de riuiere, a kind of tree
Vne Truite, poiſſon, a fiſhe called a trout.
Petite Truye, Truyette, a little ſowe.
Les Tuberoſitez des os, The roūdneſſe within the knitting of the bones.
Tuer aucun, to kill, to ſlaye, too murther.
Tuer cruellement, to kill cruelly, to murther.
Qui eſt Tué, which is killed.
Tueur de gens, a man queller, a murtherer.
Tuph, ou Tuf ſorte de pierre, a kind of ſtone.
Turbit, herbe, an herbe called Turbit.
Turquoyſe, pierre pretieuſe, a precious ſtone called a Turkis.
Tuyau, A pype, a reede, a Canell.
Tyran, vn mauuais & cruel roy ou ſeigneur, a tyrant, a cruel King.
VA par cy, goe this way.
La choſe va bien, this geare goeth well.
Vacation, ou eſtat, vacation or estate.
Vne Vache pleine, a cowe with calfe.
Du Vaciet, a kinde of purple flowre.
Vne Vague, a waue of the ſea.
Vaguer & aller ça & là, de coſté & d'aultre, to wauer, too remoue from one place too another.
Vaincre, to win, to ouercome, to ſurmount.
Vaiſſeau à vin, ou laict, a wyne veſſell.
Vallet ou Varlet, a Page, a ſeruant.
Vallet de chambre, a grome of the chamber.
Vallet de cuiſine, grome of the kitchen.
Vallet d'huis, c'eſt vn engin qui ferme l'huis, a deuiſe too ſhut a dore after one.
Valoir, to be worth, to be of value or worth.
cela vault & ſert autāt que loy, that is as good as a lawe.
Il Vault mieux que, &c. Jt is better that.
Il Vault mieux d'aller à luy, Jt is better to goe to him.
Eſtre plus Valable, to bee more worth, of greater price.
Se Vanter, to vaunt or boast.
Vn Vāteur & glorieux, a bragger, a boaster.
Vaquer & entendre à quelque choſe, that can intend to doe a thing.
Vacation d'office, the vacation of an office.
Varier & deſguiſer, faire autre, to alter or change a thing.
Varier, dire puis d'vn puis d'autre, to vary, to hold on both ſydes.
Vne Vaſe, ou Vaiſſeau, a Ʋeſſell.
Vaſſal, qui tient quelque choſe d'aucun à foy & hommage, a Ʋaſſall, who oweth hōmage by tenour.
Vancrer ſur la mer, too rowe on the ſea.
Vaultneant, an vnthrift, one that is nothing worth.
Vn vaultour, eſpece d'oiſeau de proye, a grype.
Se Veauter en la boue, to wallow in the myre.
Veeller, eſt, quand la vache fait ſon petit veau, to calue.
De la veillere, ou Liſet, herbe, an herbe called byndweed.
Robbe de Velours, A veluet gowne.
Vendoiſe, poiſſon, a kind of fiſh
Mettre en Vente quelque choſe, to put a thing to ſale.
Expoſé en Vente, putte out too ſale.
Venerable, digne qu'on luy face reuerence, & qu'on l'honore, worſhipfull.
Venger, to reuenge, to wreake, to auenge.
Venir & approcher, to come, to approch nigh.
Venir & arriuer, to come and arriue.
Venir à rien, to come to naught.
Venir deuant, to come before, to preuent.
Venir au deuant, to come and meete one.
Venir en bruit & auoir nom, to come to a name.
Venir tout à poinct, to come in ſeaſon, to come in the nicke.
Il vente, it venteth, it bloweth.
Flux de Ventre, the flixe, the laxe.
Ventrée, ce que la mere port en ſon ventre, the burthen of a womans wombe.
Vne ventoſe, a vent in a caue.
Le Ventre, the belly, the wombe.
Veoir, to ſee, to looke, to ſpie.
On le voit, it is ſeene.
Qui a eſté veu, which hath bene ſeene.
La veüe, the ſight, the vewe.
Vn ver de Poëte, a Poets verſe.
Du veratre, herbe, an herbe called Helleborus.
Verdier, vn ſort de crapault ou grenouille de hayrs, aucuns l'appellent Graiſſet, a kinde of hedge frog or tode.
Verdier, ou foreſtier, a foster, or woodman.
Verdoyer, to waxe greene, to flouriſh.
Verdon, petit oiſeau qui nourit les petits d'vne aultre penſant qu'ils ſoyent ſiens, a hedge ſparrow.
Poignée de Verges, a handfull of roddes.
Verifier & ratifier, Too verifie and ratifie.
Veritable, a true man, an vpright man.
Du Vermillon, vermilliō, a kind of red color made of quicke-ſiluer.
Vermine, toute ſorte de petites beſtes qui s'engendrent de pourriture, vermine, all ſorte of ſmall beaſts that are engendred of filth.
se Vermoulir, to mould or wax rotten.
Verole, ou rougeole de petits enfants, the ſmall pockes.
La groſſe Verole, The Frenche pockes.
Vn Verroüil, a bolt of a dore.
Verrouiller l'huis, Too bolt the dore.
Vne Verruë & petit morceau de chair eſleuée ſus le corps, a warte.
Vers la fin, towardes the ende.
Regarde Vers moy, looke towardes mee.
Verſer ou conuerſer auec aucū, to be conuerſant with one.
Vertau, Tampon, ou Bondon, a ſtopple, a bung.
La Vertebre & os de l'eſchino du dos, the chyne bone.
Auoir force & Vertu, too haue ſtrength and power.
Verueu à prendre poiſſon, A dragge.
De la Veſce, fitches, a kind of pulſe.
Veſtir, to clothe, to put on.
Veſtu de robbe de ſoye, clothed with a ſilke garment.
Veſture, a clothing, a putting on.
Veu, ou A ce que tu me racomptes, ſeeing either to that that thou tellest mee.
Veu l'heure du iour, ſeeing the howre of the day.
Vexer & tormenter, to vexe, to tormente.
Eſtre Vexé & tormēté de gens de ſa maiſon meſme, Too bee vexed and tormented with his owne houſhold.
Viagier, Rente viaigiere, During ones lyfe, a rente during ones lyfe.
Rapporter la Victoire, to carry away the victorie.
Victuailles pour vne armée, vittayles for an armie.

Vignottes, & fleurs en Liures imprimés ou enluminés, la taille, drapperie, ou feillages qu'on faict en menuizerie, ou pierres, certayne flowers or deckings printed in bookes, alſo braunches in any other kind of worke.
Vendre a vil pris, to ſel for lowe price.
Vileté, ou Vieut • , bon & grande marche de toutes choſes, good cheape of any thing.
Vilener & enlaidir, to raye or defile.
Vn villageois, a man of the countrie.
Ville, ou cité, a towne or citie.
Villoter, to run from one towne to another.
Vn Villotier, a lande loper, a runagate.
Les villes, fleaux, ou tendons de la vigne, the yong braunches of the vine.
Vin de preſſourage, the after preſſed wine.
Le vin des vallets, ſeruaunts wine.
Vinot, Vinet, petit Vin, ſmall wine.
Vn Vinotier, Tauernier, a vintener, a tauerner.
Vinette, ou ozeille ſauuage, wilde ſ • rrell.
Violer vne fille, to rauiſhe a maide, to defloure.
Violier, a violer or player on the violl.
Vipere, vne ſorte de ſerpent, a kinde of ſerpent called a Viper.
Vne vire, ou traict d'arbaleſte a quarrell for a Croſſebowe.
Virement, vireuouſtes, turning, friskes or gamboles.
Vis de preſſoir, ou maiſon à monter par degrez, the vice of a preſſe, or turning of a paire of ſtaires.
Vis à vis, face to face, ouer against.
Viſer bien droict, ou frapper dedens le blanc, to l • uell right, to hit the white.
Qui ne viſe point à l'aduenir, that regardeth not the tyme to come.
Viſible, viſible, that may be ſene
Vital, qui à vie, vitall, that hath lyfe.
Vituperer & blaſmer, to reuile, or blame one.
Vn Viuier ou eſtang, a ponde.
S'il euſt Veſcu, if hee had liued.
Vn ou deux, one or twoo.
Ce m'eſt tout Vn, it is all one to mee.
Vnir, to vnite, to ſet at one.
Vniement & applaniſſement, making playne and ſmooth.
Voarrier, Verrier, ou Vitrier, a glaſier.
La Voile d'vne nauire, the ſayle of a ſhip.
Voiler, couurir & cacher, Too vayle, to couer, to hyde.
Voire dea: Ouy dea, mot dict par mocquerie, yea wiſſe.
Voiries d'vne ville, the lay ſtall of a towne.
La voix des eſliſants en la creation de quelque office, The voyce of the chooſers.
Le Vol des oyſeaus, the flying of birds.
Faire quelque choſe à la Volée, to doo a thing at all aduentures.
Parler à la Volée, to ſpeake at randon.
Volage, a ſhittle hedded fellow, an inconstant man.
Voliere, a birde cage, or where birds be brought vp.
Voltiger vn cheual, too manage a horſe.
Vn Volume & partie d'vn Liure, A volume or part of a booke.
Volunté, Voluntiers, Volōtaire Volontairemēt, ſeeke vouloir.
Vomir, to parbreake, to vomite, to ſpue.
Le Veu que les anciens faiſoyent an Diable, the vowe that men of old tyme made too the Diuel.
Vouge, a hunting ſtaffe, a boare ſpeare.
Le Vouloir & intention, the wil and intent.
La Volonté ou vouloir d'aucū, the wil of one.
Volontaire, that is of oure owne free will.
Voy-cy, Voy-là, cōme qui diroit Voy-le cy, Voy-le là, here, there, ſee here, ſee there.
vne Voye ou Voicture de quelque choſe, The weight of a thing.
Suiuir la Voye & l'exemple, To follow the waye or example of other.
Le Voyer, the bounds of landes.
C'eſt vn Vray calomniateur, it is a very wrangler.
Vray ſemblance, likely too bee true.
Sçauoir au vray, to knowe certainly.
Vrbanité, Ciuilité, good maner, vrbanitie, courteſie.
Vriner, to make water, to piſſe.
Vn Vrinal, a chamber pot, an vrinal.

Vne Vrne, ancien vaiſſeau de terre ayant le col eſtroict, ſeruant à porter & garder l'eaue cōme vne cruche: Seruant auſſi anciennement au Preteur à mettre le nom des Iuges & des parties quand il failloit vuider quelque choſe par ſort: Et à mettre & garder les cendres des treſpaſſez, an earthen veſſel with a narrowe necke that ſerued to keepe water in as in a pot, it ſerued the magistats alſo to put in the names when they ſhould decide any thing by lot, and alſo to preſerue the asſhes of the dead.
Vſiter & exerciter ſa memoire, to vſe or exerciſe the memorie.
Bien Vſité aux liures, wel exerciſed at his booke.
Vſance, ou Vſage, vſance, vſury, wearing or vſe.
Vſufruict, droict d'vſage & iouiſſance ſus les choſes, dont la proprieté appertient à aultruy, an vſurping of an other mans ground and reaping the fruites thereof.
Vſure de ſouliers, wearing oute of ſhoes.
Vtenſile, toute choſe neceſſaire à noſtre vſage, any kinde of toole that a man doth occupie.
Fay Vuyder ceſte tourbe, cauſe this people to auoyde.
Droict & Vz de franchiſe, the right and custome of a freedome.
Aux vs & couſtume, To the vſe and customes.
YA il choſe quoy ie vous puiſſe ſeruir? Js there any thing wherein J maye do you ſeruice.
Yeux qui ſe mouuent ça & là, rolling eyes.
Arbre nommé Yf, an ewe tree.
Le cours de l'Yuer, the courſe of winter.
Yuoire ou Iuoire, dent d'Elephant, Yuory, Elephants, tooth.
Qui eſt d'Yuoire, That is of Yuorie.
ZEle, comme Qui ont Zele, zeale, that be zelous.
Zephyre, vent d'Occident, qui cōmence à ſouffler au printemps, lequel faict germer toute plante, the VVest winde.
Le Zodiaque, Cercle au ciel ou ſont les douze ſignes, The zodiake or the circle in which the twelue ſignes be placed.
Zizanie, Toute ſemence baſtar de, qui croiſt parmy le bon blé, autrement appellée Yuroye, coccle.

div.p: Imprinted at London, by Henry Bynneman, For Lucas Harriſon. An. 1570.
